Addis Ababa.

while preparations are underway to establish isolation centers in Adama, Shashemene, Yabelo, and Nekemte

Precaution

Oromiya Regional Health Bureau and PHEM provided training on COVID-19 preparedness and readiness for health officials drawn from zonal and district health offices and as well as for hospitals. In addition, isolation centers established in Bishoftu and Jimma Towns,

The process has been started to start the screening process at Lalibela, Gonder, and Kombolcha airports.
•Screening is conducted at Dire Dawa International Airport and Dawale land crossing and an isolation center have been established.

In addition to the screening program at Gog, Dima, Lare, Wantawo & Jikawo, an isolation center has been prepared at Gambela in coordination with the regional hospitals.
In Amhara a screening process has been continued at Metema land crossing and Bahir dar International Airport.

•Training has been given to all regions rapid response team
•In collaboration with Hawassa University, an isolation center has been established in Hawassa town. In addition to this, the same preparation activities have been started at Jinka and Arba Minch towns.

to every airport with especial consideration to tourist destination areas, to establish a rapid response team & follow up team @ each region to facilitate the follow up of passengers at their respective residence and conducting training to increase the capacity of health workers.

Activities have been carried out to replicate and align the national structure to regional and lower administrative structures. These activities emphasize on preparing and equipping isolation center in each region, to expand the screening programs from the international airports

Regional preparation for COVID -19
Involvement and preparation of the regions in preparing towards preparedness, early detection and response with regards to COVID-19 is an essential step in making the response activity effective and efficient.

Screening at Galafi land crossing in Afar region has been initiated. Equipping and capacitate the isolation and treatment centers have been continued Drill exercises to upgrade the skill of the health workers have been carried out regularly to strengthen the preparedness activity

Passengers with a history of travel to Korea, Japan, the Islamic Republic of Iran and Italy were included under the follow up after filling the health declaration form. a consultant from WHO has visited the influenza laboratory in EPHI & approved it is in full capacity to do test

• Training on preparedness for COVID-19 provided for mgt & professionals invited from various industrial parks
The health section staff of the Chinese Embassy met with EPHI & discussed on how to collaboratively work on the prevention of  COVID-19 followed by visiting the EOC

Since the past press release on February 25, 2020
•There was a total of forty-seven thousand five hundred forty-five (47,545) passengers that have passed through the screening points at all entries.

All of the suspected cases were tested negative and released from the Centre. There has been a total of three thousand nine hundred twenty-two (3,922) calls made to the toll-free line 8335, from which one thousand three hundred forty (1,340) were COVID -19 related.

A total number of eighty-two (82) rumors were received by EPHI’s Emergency Operation Center (EOC) and all have been investigated. Out of these rumors, twenty (20) had symptoms similar to COVID-19 and were in the Isolation Centre until their laboratory results proved.

Two hundred twenty thousand three hundred fifty-seven (220,357) passengers have passed the seven screening gates at Bole International Airport (BIA). Out of these five thousand four hundred seventy-six (5,476) are from countries that reported COVID-19 cases.

የአራማውር ሐንሰን የምርምር ኢንስቲቲዩት 50ኛ ዓመት የምስረታ ቀን በማስመልከት የኢንስቲቲዩቱ ዋና ዳይሬክተር ዶ/ር አበበ ገነቱ ለተሳታፊዎቹ አጠር ያለ ገለጻ አድርገው የበዓሉ አከባበር በቀጣይ ጊዜያት በተለያዩ ሁነቶች እንደሚቀጥል ጠቁመዋል፡፡
በጤና ኤክስቴንሽን ቀጣይ ሂደት ላይ የተጀመሩ ስራዎች አዲስ እየተዘጋጀ ባለው ፍኖተ ካርታ በጥልቀት እንደሚፈተሸ ጠቁመው ሚኒስቴር መስሪያ ቤቱም ለጤና ኤክስቴንሽን ባለሙያዎችና ለስራው ትኩረት ሰጥቶ በኃላፊነት ስራውን እንደሚከታተል ገልጸዋል፡፡
ሁለተኛው የጤናው ዘርፍ የትራንስፎርሜሽን እቅድ ለማዘጋጀት የሚደረገውን ጥረትና ተግባር በመነሻ ጥናትና በአዳዲስ አሰራሮች በሚገባ ተፈትሾ መከናወን ይገባዋል ብለዋል፡፡
ሚኒስትሩ አያይዘውም በየቡድኖቹ የቀረቡትን ጠቃሚ ነጥቦች በማደራጀት በዌብሳይት ስለሚወጡ በቀጣይም የጤናውዘርፍ አባላት አስተያየታቸውን እንዲሰጡበት አሳስበው
ሁሉም ክልሎች ለዚሁ ስኬት እንዲረባረቡ ጥሪ አቅርበዋል፡፡ከሌሎች የሚኒስቴር መስሪያ ቤቶች ጋር በመቀናጀት ለሚከናወነው ዘርፈ ብዙ የጋራ ተግባርም በ100 ወረዳዎች ላይ እውን ለማድረግ መታቀዱን ተናግረዋል፡፡
እና ሌሎችም ርዕሰ ጉዳዮችን በማንሳት በቀጣይ ለሚከናወኑ ተግባራት ስንቅ የሚሆኑ ነጥቦች ተገኝተዋል፡፡የጤና ሚኒስትሩ በጉባኤው ማጠቃለያ ላይ እንደገለጹት  በ2012 ዓ.ም 150 ወረዳዎች ትራንስፎርም እንዲያደርጉ ቃል መገባቱን አስታውሰው
በሰባት ቡድኖች ተከፋፍለው የተወያዩት ተሳታፊዎች በተለይ በወረዳ ትራንስፎርሜሽን፤በጤና ኤክስቴንሽን ፕሮግራም  የጥናት ውጤት፤ በሁለተኛው የጤናው ዘርፍ  ስትራቴጂክ እቅድ፤በአዕምሮ ጤና፤ በቲቢ፤በቆላ በሽታዎች፤በክትባት፤ ያገባኛል /I-CARE/
ከሁለቱ የከተማ አስተዳደሮች ፤ ከጤና ሚኒስቴር፤ ከተጠሪ ተቋማትና አጋር ድርጅቶች የተውጣጡ ከ900 በላይ ተሳታፊዎችን ለአራት ቀናት ያስተናገደው ገባኤው ባለፉት ሁለት ቀናት በቡድን ውይይት በመሳተፍ ለቀጣይ ስራ አጋዥ የሆኑ ነጥቦችን አንስተዋል፡

በተለያዩ የጤናው ዘርፍ አጀንዳዎች ላይ ሲመክር የቆየው ገባኤ ተጠናቀቀ
በአዲስ አበባ ስካይ ላይት ሆቴል በተለያዩ የጤናው ዘርፍ አጀንዳዎች ላይ ሲመክር የቆየው 21ኛው ዓመታዊ ገባኤ ዛሬ ፍጻሜውን አግኝቷል፡፡ከዘጠኙ ክልሎችና
የአዕምሮ ጤና፣ ተላላፊ ያልሆኑ በሽታዎች፣ ቲቢ እና የተዘነጉ የቆላ በሽታዎች  ላይ ዙሪያ ከባለሙያዎች፣ ከባለድርሻ አካላት ፣ ከማህበራት እና አጋር የልማት ድርጅቶች ጋር  ውይይት ተደረገ ፡፡
21ኛውን የጤና ዘርፍ ዓመታዊ ጉባኤ ምክንያት በማድረግ ከጤና ሚኒስቴር እና ከክልሎች የተውጣጡ  የጤናው ዘርፍ አመራሮችና ባለሙያዎች  የኢትዮጵያ ሕብረተሰብ ጤና ኢንስቲትዩት የምርምር ላቡራቶሪዎችን በዛሬው ዕለት ጉብኙ፡፡#ARM2019
